      "Crane damage documented with photographs"
    ],
    "summary": "On 18-AUG-2021 at 1300 hours, a contract crane operator employed by Danos was performing a pre-use inspection of a crane on platform AC-CMP at Grand Isle Block 43. While raising the boom at high throttle to test the high angle kickout, the operator reached down with his left hand to grab a rag to handle the hot swing lever. The high angle kickout valve failed to activate, allowing the boom to continue rising past its normal stopping point. The boom struck the boom stop at high throttle, resulting in the boom bending over the top of the crane. The estimated damage was $100,000. No injuries occurred.",
    "recommendations": [],
